==English==

===Etymology===
From {{etyl|ang}} {{term|hwil|hwīl|lang=ang}}, from {{proto|gem-pro|hwīlō|lang=en}}. Cognate with {{etyl|nds|-}} {{term|wil|lang=nds}}.

===Pronunciation===
* {{a|UK}} {{IPA|/ʍaɪl/}}, {{X-SAMPA|/WaIl/}}
* {{a|US}} {{IPA|/waɪl/}}, {{X-SAMPA|/waIl/}}
* {{audio|en-us-while.ogg|Audio (US)}}
* {{rhymes|aɪl}}

===Noun===
{{en-noun}}

# A certain duration of time, a period of time.
#: ''He lectured for quite a long '''while'''.''

